Exercise C O-word subroutines, including parameter passing and return values.

Re-expressed for gomc: the classic test called Python O-word subroutines
(o<square>, o<multiply>) with fixed and variable argument counts and read the
result back as #<_value>.  gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter, so the
subs are C interp_ext O-words (cmod test_oword_math, register_oword).  The driver
calls them via MDI; checkresult greps the cmod log to confirm the arguments were
passed through (fixed + variable count) and — by feeding a prior call's #<_value>
back in as an argument — that the return value round-tripped into the interpreter.
